  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are actively selling into this 5.9% surge as SPX pushes through the massive +2.2B gamma wall at 6575, creating natural resistance and likely capping further upside momentum in the near-term. The PIN regime with spot sitting right at max positive gamma (6575) means dealers will continue to fade this rally by selling calls and hedging short, providing a strong headwind for bulls. Watch for mean reversion back toward the 6560-6565 support cluster where dealers will flip to buying, but any break above 6580 (+1.7B wall) would signal more aggressive dealer selling and potential exhaustion.",
